---
id: org.dxos.plugin.extension
name: ExtensionPlugin
version: 0.1.0
---

Exposes user settings for the `@dxos/composer-crx` browser extension. Owns the
user-facing settings surface for the extension's search render-proxy: fetching
and JS-rendering pages in a real browser tab so plugins (e.g. product search)
can scrape client-rendered or anti-bot sites a plain HTTP proxy cannot read.

Settings are persisted via the app-framework settings store and exposed to
other plugins through a plugin-scoped capability so they can decide whether to
route a fetch through the extension or the edge proxy.

## Extensions

The following extension dialects are used in this document.
Each extension is defined in the Appendix or resolved via its URI.

| Term   | URI                            |
|--------|--------------------------------|
| `type` | `org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0`        |
| `feat` | `org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0`        |
| `test` | `org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0`        |

## Types

```mdl
type Settings
  desc: |
    User preferences governing how Composer uses the composer-crx extension as
    a search render-proxy. Persisted via the app-framework settings store. All
    fields are optional; defaults are documented per field.
  fields:
    renderProxyEnabled?: boolean  # default: true. Master switch: when false,
                                  # plugins use the edge HTTP proxy instead.
    renderTimeout?: number        # default: 20000. Max ms to wait for a render.
    renderActiveTab?: boolean     # default: false. Render in a focused tab.
    developerMode?: boolean       # default: false. Verbose logging / previews.
```

## Features

```mdl
feat Settings
  desc: Surface the extension settings in the standard Composer settings panel.
  req:
    - The plugin contributes a settings surface under the app settings panel.
    - Settings persist across reloads via the app-framework settings store.
    - The Settings atom is exposed under a plugin-scoped capability for readers.

test Settings
  desc: The settings schema round-trips and applies documented defaults.
  steps:
    - Reading settings with no stored value yields the documented defaults.
    - Setting a field and re-reading returns the updated value merged over defaults.
```
